# NOVA Master Philosophy

NOVA is an **EXPERIENCE**, not an LMS. Every screen, label, and interaction must feel like stepping into a living mission — not opening Moodle, Canvas, or a course catalog.

## Core Identity

- NOVA = guided exploration + discovery + building — never passive reading
- Students are **Explorers** on **Missions**, not pupils in **Lessons**
- The platform should feel like Pixar storytelling + Apple polish + NASA mission control
- Interfaces must feel **alive** (motion, warmth, personality) — never static admin panels

## Explorer First (North Star)

**Every decision filters through one question:**

> **Does this make the Explorer feel capable, excited, and supported?**

Explorers should never feel tested, lost, or like they're in a gradebook. They should feel like **mission heroes** with a crew behind them — Buddies, Innovation Mentors, and a universe that celebrates trying.

- Celebrate progress, not perfection
- Offer a path when hardware isn't available (simulation counts)
- Mentor sessions = showcase + troubleshooting, not judgment
- Copy speaks *to* the Explorer with warmth, never *at* them with syllabus tone

## Emotional Goal

Every NOVA experience should evoke **wonder, curiosity, and joy**.

The Explorer should think: *"I don't want to leave."*

Design for delight first. Learning follows engagement.

## The 2-Hour Test

Before shipping any NOVA-facing screen, ask:

> **Would a child voluntarily spend two hours here?**

If the answer is no — redesign before adding features.

## Every Screen Must Answer

1. **Why am I here?** — Clear purpose, not buried in nav
2. **What's today's mission?** — One exciting objective, not a syllabus
3. **Why is this exciting?** — Stakes, story, or discovery hook

## Language Rules (User-Facing NOVA Experiences)

**USE:** Mission, Quest, Discovery, Adventure, Explorer, LAB, Achievement, Buddy, Signal, Rover, Breakthrough

**NEVER USE** in NOVA experience UI:
- Lesson 1 / Lesson 2 / Lesson 3
- "Start Lesson", "Course module", "Complete the reading"
- Syllabus-style numbering or academic catalog copy

| BAD | GOOD |
|-----|------|
| Lesson 3: Introduction to Variables | Mission: Decode the Signal |
| Start Lesson | Launch Mission |
| Course | Mission Path |
| Quiz | Innovation Check |
| Enrolled Courses (in experience context) | Active Missions |
| Browse all courses | Explore Mission Board |

Backend routes (`/courses`, `courseSlug`) may stay internal — **labels** must speak mission universe.

## Buddy Companion Rules

- Buddies are **real characters** with emotional attachment — not emoji placeholders
- All buddy portraits: **forward-facing**, looking at the Explorer
- Use `<img>` with `object-fit: cover` and `object-position: center top`
- Reuse `BuddyAvatar` component — do not render emoji for buddies

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — emoji buddy
<div className="text-6xl">{buddy.emoji}</div>

// ✅ GOOD — real portrait
<BuddyAvatar src={buddy.image} alt={`${buddy.name}, NOVA Buddy`} size="card" />
```

```css
.buddy-portrait {
  object-fit: cover;
  object-position: center top;
}
```

## Learning Model

- **Explore** → poke, try, observe
- **Discover** → "aha" moments from doing, not reading
- **Build** → hands-on LABs, not walls of text

Content delivery:
- Short mission briefings, not lectures
- Interactive stations, not PDFs
- Reflection after action, not reading before action

## What Must NEVER Exist (NOVA Experiences)

- PDF downloads as primary content
- Walls of text / long reading blocks
- Boring multiple-choice quizzes with no story
- Dead screens with no next action
- Generic LMS chrome (module lists, gradebook feel)
- Emoji avatars for NOVA Buddies

## Design Philosophy

Combine:
- **Pixar** — character, warmth, narrative arc
- **Apple** — clarity, polish, intentional whitespace
- **NASA** — mission briefing, progress, achievement ceremony

Motion and micro-interactions should reinforce progress — not decorate emptiness.

## Developer Checklist (NOVA Experience Work)

When touching `src/components/experiences/*`, `src/app/experiences/*`, or `src/lib/experiences/*`:

- [ ] Copy uses Mission/Quest/Discovery language
- [ ] Buddy images are real portraits, forward-facing
- [ ] Screen answers: why here, today's mission, why exciting
- [ ] No lesson-numbering or course-catalog tone
- [ ] Passes the 2-hour voluntary engagement test
- [ ] Interactive element present — not read-only content

## Hardware & Mentor-Led Builds (Arduino / ESP32)

Official kit: **NOVA Explorer Kit (ESP32)** — see `src/lib/nova-kit.ts`.  
Mentor-led mission metadata: `src/lib/pathways/mentor-missions.ts`.

- Robotics + IoT build missions use **ESP32** (Arduino IDE) — one base kit, optional Robotics Add-On
- Mentor-led LABs/PROJECTs get **Explorer Mission** banners with encouragement + checkpoints
- Always include **Wokwi fallback** so Explorers without hardware still belong
- Innovation Mentors review at monthly sessions — frame as *celebration*, not audit

## Scope Note

The broader LMS (`/courses`, admin, enrollments) may retain course terminology until migrated. **Prioritize** experience player, catalog, homepage CTA, and Explorer Portal sections for mission language.
